    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A warm brownish red color of various values, originally referring to the color of sienna pigment, which is derived from soil and used as a pigment in oil and watercolor painting.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046693/Merriam-Webster's Collegiate Dictionary [online] (1997-2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Warme bruinachtige rode kleur met uiteenlopende kleurwaarden, verwees oorspronkelijk naar de kleur van siena-pigment, dat uit aarde wordt gewonnen en als pigment wordt gebruikt bij het schilderen met olie- of waterverf.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
